Thriving Under Pressure: Stress Manageme.objectives:
At the end of the activity, students will be able to:
1. Understand the nature of stress, its causes, and how it affects mental and physical well-being; 
2. Identify common stressors faced by university students, such as academic demands, time management, and social pressures; 
3. Learn effective stress management techniques, including mindfulness, relaxation exercises, and time prioritization; 
4. Develop personalized strategies for maintaining a healthy balance between academic responsibilities and self-care; and 
5. Build resilience and enhance coping skills to navigate university life with confidence and clarity.

